{"TopicId":157535,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"SAS: Hold Horizon","CreatedByName":"MajorNr01","CreatedById":43823,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-09T21:14:58Z","PageNum":5,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JonathanPerregaux","CreatedById":152561,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-13T18:17:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI use MechJeb\u0027s Smart A.S.S. mode or Atmosphere Autopilot to hold a horizon lock. It\u0027sa verra naaaice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DeltaDizzy","CreatedById":150755,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-13T23:44:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223117466\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499762946\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022175796\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mabdi36\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/11/2017 at 3:49 AM, mabdi36 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223119971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499969623\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NSEP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, NSEP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223119424\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499917000\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154075\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022User name\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, User name said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*snip\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223118715\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499872745\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022172955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u002253miner53\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/12/2017 at 10:19 AM, 53miner53 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPART TWO!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis needs to exist.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stoney3K","CreatedById":139954,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-16T15:02:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222981543\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489136864\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10-3-2017 at 10:07 AM, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstead of just this one special case, I would support a generic \u0027Hold Current Navball Pitch and Roll Angles\u0027 setting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis would provide what you request for the one special case of the horizon (zero pitch angle), plus any other pitch up or down angles one would wish for a controlled ascent/descent/reentry situation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo keep in mind that (especially for aircraft), pitch and roll does not have to equal flight path angle (the angle between your horizontal and vertical speed, or the surface prograde vector)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is only the case where zero pitch will cause your aircraft to remain straight and level. If you want to make it more generic, a \u0027flight path angle hold\u0027 feature on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E would be great. That means that pitch adjusts according to airspeed (pitching down when the craft speeds up, and pitching up when the craft slows down) to maintain the correct vertical speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am very much in favor of a feature that can maintain FPA since it is very useful for any mode of surface flight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerBlitz Kerman","CreatedById":178055,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-16T18:53:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this as well as auto-grav turn and hold vert as well. Auto land would be a Kerbal saver as well as.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-16T20:24:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI still support this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SinisterSonar","CreatedById":184233,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T04:14:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T08:05:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223119591\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499940621\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022177832\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022PaperAviator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/13/2017 at 0:10 PM, PaperAviator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@Blaarkies\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah I really didn\u0027t think that through\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe you are on to something...what if it locks to the navball, but does not get affected by the yaw action as you pass over the poles?\u003Cbr\u003E\nAs in, it actually locks to a vector relative to the stars, but this vector gets continually updated by the \u0022pitch curve\u0022 of the planet(so that airplanes do not end up pointing upwards)\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe navball heading will definitely rotate as you change latitude, but we aren\u0027t concerned with that. Come to think about it, it sounds like using the surface velocity vector, rotating the vector reference to the\u00A0\u0022up\u0022 vector(away from gravity), and then replacing the pitch scalar with the locked value\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DunaManiac","CreatedById":176003,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T21:55:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerBlitz Kerman","CreatedById":178055,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-18T03:20:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSupported, everybody put it in your Sig.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-18T04:17:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223122728\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221500231186\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022178055\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KerBlitz Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/16/2017 at 2:53 PM, KerBlitz Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this as well as auto-grav turn and hold vert as well. Auto land would be a Kerbal saver as well as.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHold vertical = \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:radial:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/Radial20px.png\u0022 title=\u0022:radial:\u0022\u003E\u00A0......\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspa