 the unofficial official \u0022I support this\u0022 record keeper.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-18T06:26:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223124137\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221500351455\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JadeOfMaar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, JadeOfMaar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHold vertical = \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:radial:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/Radial20px.png\u0022 title=\u0022:radial:\u0022\u003E\u00A0......\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/178055-kerblitz-kerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022178055\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/178055-kerblitz-kerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@KerBlitz Kerman\u003C/a\u003E Change navball to \u0022Surface mode\u0022, set \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E to hold radial-out...it wont actually aim at radial, but will aim at \u0022Up\u0022/\u0022vertical\u0022. This is really useful for powered landing as well:\u003Cbr\u003E\n-Having almost zero vertical speed, makes the retrograde marker jump around the horizon, and a ship following that marker becomes a disaster.\u003Cbr\u003E\n-Switching to surface mode, and to hold radial-out will keep the ship upright. You can then just slightly tilt away from the direction of your horizontal speed\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-18T06:27:37Z\u0022 title=\u002207/18/2017 06:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 18, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Blaarkies\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerBlitz Kerman","CreatedById":178055,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-18T13:49:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThx \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/153700-blaarkies/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022153700\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/153700-blaarkies/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Blaarkies\u003C/a\u003E, and \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JadeOfMaar\u003C/a\u003E, that will help for my \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E adventures!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ourworldalpha1","CreatedById":160913,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-18T17:01:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stoney3K","CreatedById":139954,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-23T19:29:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223124189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221500359202\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153700\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Blaarkies\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 18-7-2017 at 8:26 AM, Blaarkies said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/178055-kerblitz-kerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022178055\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/178055-kerblitz-kerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@KerBlitz Kerman\u003C/a\u003E Change navball to \u0022Surface mode\u0022, set \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E to hold radial-out...it wont actually aim at radial, but will aim at \u0022Up\u0022/\u0022vertical\u0022. This is really useful for powered landing as well:\u003Cbr\u003E\n-Having almost zero vertical speed, makes the retrograde marker jump around the horizon, and a ship following that marker becomes a disaster.\u003Cbr\u003E\n-Switching to surface mode, and to hold radial-out will keep the ship upright. You can then just slightly tilt away from the direction of your horizontal speed\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis also means that you can make a craft hold straight and level by putting a probe core (or docking port) on its roof and tracking \u0022\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E Radial Out\u0022. The craft will then keep flying wings level, nose forward.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomething that has a little more precision or repeatability would actually be nice. I use MechJeb\u0027s Smart ASS because I can just enter attitude values numerically and change attitude one axis at a time, so I can keep control of my pitch vector while the heading stays locked, so the craft will get in orbit on the proper inclination. I hardly use any other feature from MechJeb, but the Smart ASS is great because you can follow the same launch profile for every mission, instead of having to guesstimate your attitude from the navball and correct with WASD.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"thereaverofdarkness2","CreatedById":158940,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-24T01:07:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to see it be a toggle on the navball. When it\u0027s set to atmospheric flight, it\u0027ll have horizontal prograde/retrograde markers, up/down markers, and horizontal sideways markers. These would replace the orbital markers that you see on the orbital navball. When you use the atmospheric flight navball, your Kerbal or probe core pilots would follow the new markers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal101","CreatedById":157058,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-11T23:12:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPilot Assistant, while great is still a bit over the top, it binds to tab... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E I\u0027d appreciate just Hold vertical Speed. So\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#3498db;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EI support this\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheKSPBeginner","CreatedById":154786,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-19T19:15:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Comic Sans MS\u0027, cursive;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003EI support this\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerbolExplorer","CreatedById":177191,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-20T12:14:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Ei support this\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-20T17:48:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Persistent Rotation mod can keep rotation constant relative to a planet\u0027s surface, both in warp mode and physics mode.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-08-20T17:49:12Z\u0022 title=\u002208/20/2017 05:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 20, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Enceos\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-20T20:48:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223153166\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221503251335\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Enceos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Enceos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Persistent Rotation mod can keep rotation constant relative to a planet\u0027s surface, both in warp mode and physics mode.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat does just about nothing for the primary use case for this idea: atmospheric craft.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Also, I believe Persistent Rotation keeps rotation constant in the inertial reference frame rather than the rotating reference frame.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotaru","CreatedById":135669,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-20T20:52:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223153300\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221503262091\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat does just about nothing for the primary use case for this idea: atmospheric craft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy impression is it actually\u003Cem\u003E does\u003C/em\u003E work for atmospheric craft: it lets you use regular \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E to hold attitude relative to the horizon instead of relative to the sun, which doesn\u0027t work in stock KSP. Which is to say, in stock KSP a plane flying level will be pointing straight up after flying a quarter of the way around the planet--with Persistent Rotation, it\u0027d still be flying level.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t do much good if you\u0027re on console, and doesn\u0027t make this any less a good suggestion for the stock game, but if you\u0027re OK with mods Persistent Rotation does help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-21T21:19:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223153302\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221503262344\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135669\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hotaru\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/20/2017 at 6:22 PM, Hotaru said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy impression is it actually\u003Cem\u003E does\u003C/em\u003E work for atmospheric craft: it lets you use regular \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E to hold attitude relative to the horizon instead of relative to the sun, which doesn\u0027t work in stock KSP. Which is to say, in stock KSP a plane flying level will be pointing straight up after flying a quarter of the way around the planet--with Persistent Rotation, it\u0027d still be flying level.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t do much good if you\u0027re on console, and doesn\u0027t make this any less a good suggestion for the stock game, but if you\u0027re OK with mods Persistent Rotation does help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s not what Persistent Rotation does, to my understanding. It closes the loophole of rotation stopping during timewarp, but doesn\u0027t change reference frames or anything. It doesn\u0027t do anything with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E as far as I know.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat said, I haven\u0027t used it in a while, maybe the scope of the mod has changed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}